The paper proposes an optimization method for the Dark Channel Prior (DCP) dehazing algorithm, which is commonly used in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses a dataset (RESIDE) to train and test the proposed method, which falls under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The method involves building a regression model, which can be considered as a machine learning approach, and thus, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper compares the performance of the proposed method with other state-of-the-art dehazing algorithms, which involves statistical analysis, and thus, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible sub-category.
